  "page": "The Rat, the Hawk, and the Pig",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aelora_and_the_Rat_the_Hawk_and_the_Pig_by_tragedy-peanut-gallery.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6c/Aelora_and_the_Rat_the_Hawk_and_the_Pig_by_tragedy-peanut-gallery.png/350px-Aelora_and_the_Rat_the_Hawk_and_the_Pig_by_tragedy-peanut-gallery.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"467\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6c/Aelora_and_the_Rat_the_Hawk_and_the_Pig_by_tragedy-peanut-gallery.png/525px-Aelora_and_the_Rat_the_Hawk_and_the_Pig_by_tragedy-peanut-gallery.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6c/Aelora_and_the_Rat_the_Hawk_and_the_Pig_by_tragedy-peanut-gallery.png/700px-Aelora_and_the_Rat_the_Hawk_and_the_Pig_by_tragedy-peanut-gallery.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aelora_and_the_Rat_the_Hawk_and_the_Pig_by_tragedy-peanut-gallery.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Aelora_Targaryen\" title=\"Aelora Targaryen\">Aelora Targaryen</a>, and the Rat, the Hawk, and the Pig, by tragedy-peanut-gallery ©</div></div></div>\n<p><b>The Rat, the Hawk, and the Pig</b> are three men who are mentioned in the history of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. Their real names are not known.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> As their only known actions were at least thirty years apart, it may be possible that different individuals used these names at different times.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Rat,_the_Hawk,_and_the_Pig&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Some time between <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_217_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">217&#160;AC</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_221_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">221&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, these three men attacked <a href=\"/index.php/Aelora_Targaryen\" title=\"Aelora Targaryen\">Aelora Targaryen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Princess_of_Dragonstone\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Princess of Dragonstone\">Princess of Dragonstone</a>, at a masked ball. She committed suicide soon afterward.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_251_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">251&#160;AC</a>, the trio led a rebellion that was crushed by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_Targaryen_(son_of_Aegon_V)\" title=\"Daeron Targaryen (son of Aegon V)\">Daeron Targaryen</a>. Daeron perished in the final battle, alongside his lover, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jeremy_Norridge\" title=\"Jeremy Norridge\">Jeremy Norridge</a>, but the rebels were slain or hanged.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Rat,_the_Hawk,_and_the_Pig&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Cf. the <a href=\"/index.php/Vulture_King\" title=\"Vulture King\">Vulture King</a>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Rat,_the_Hawk,_and_the_Pig&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a><